message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "SCR Financial Networks: Spectral Coarse-Graining for Systemic Risk Analysis"
version: 0.3.0
date-released: 2025-07-24
url: "https://github.com/francoispzn/scr-financial-networks"
repository-code: "https://github.com/francoispzn/scr-financial-networks"
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: Petizon
    given-names: Francois
    affiliation: "Department of Informatics, King's College London"
keywords:
  - spectral-coarse-graining
  - graph-neural-networks
  - systemic-risk
  - financial-networks
  - agent-based-model
  - graph-attention-network
abstract: >-
  A framework for systemic risk analysis in financial networks combining
  spectral coarse-graining (adapting Schmidt, Caccioli & Aste 2025),
  temporal Graph Attention Networks, and multi-channel agent-based
  stress testing. Includes configurable bank universes (10-100+ banks),
  FX conversion, RMT denoising, walk-forward cross-validation, and
  an interactive Dash dashboard.
